Poor Customer Service Experience
I am writing to express my disappointment regarding a negative experience I had today at your café located at East Independence Boulevard in Indian Trail, NC (Café #601137). I am a frequent customer and usually enjoy your service, but unfortunately, this visit was very upsetting.
Today, I visited your location with my family of four. When my order (#226361) was called as ready for pickup, I noticed that it was incorrect and part of the order was missing. I approached the lady, to kindly let her know about the issue. I explained that the items I received were not what I had ordered and suggested that she double-check with the gentleman who had actually taken my order at the counter.
Instead of listening or trying to clarify, the lady made me feel as if I were lying, repeating several times that "the order doesn't say that," despite my insistence. Eventually, the gentleman who took my order came over and confirmed to her that I was indeed correct. However, she continued arguing with him in front of me, making the entire situation even more uncomfortable.
To make matters worse, I later realized that additional items were still missing from my order, and I had to go through the same process again. The attitude and behavior I encountered today were extremely disappointing. I believe customer service should prioritize respect and resolution, not confrontation. At no point did anyone apologize for the mistake or the unpleasant treatment.

I hope Panera Bread addresses this situation appropriately and provides better training to ensure that no other customer has to experience what my family and I went through today.
Sincerely,

Came here to leave a review and see what I already reviewed this place half a decade ago.   The 1-Star remains.  At least they’re consistent!       What follows was posted 5 years ago and remains true:

—-
Having eaten at dozens of Panera locations across the U.S., I know the norm.    After moving to Indian Trail, we visited this location several times and consistently found slow and sub-par service, very unclean tables, and lots of out-of-stock menu items.  None of my usual Panera meals were actually available on any visit, but each time I was told it was a  brief stock issue.   Not so.

This single location grossly misrepresents Panera service and food quality,  and damages the brand as a whole.  It’s bad enough that if it were me, I’d close the restaurant immediately.  I expect Panera to be quite good in accordance with product pricing and have been amazed at the consistency across many locations (until this one). So after three awful visits,  my options are to lower my expectations or avoid this location and continue to expect excellence from Panera (I chose the latter).

EDIT: just visited again after a 4 month avoidance.   Still 1 Star, only because that’s the minimum possible.  0 stars would be more accurate.    A number of greasy fast food joints have better food and a cleaner operation.   Disgusting!

I am writing to express my disappointment regarding a negative experience I had today at your café located at East Independence Boulevard in Indian Trail, NC (Café #601137). I am a frequent customer and usually enjoy your service, but unfortunately, this visit was very upsetting.

I approached the lady, to kindly let her know about the issue. I explained that the items I received were not what I had ordered and suggested that she double-check with the gentleman who had actually taken my order at the counter.
Instead of listening or trying to clarify, the lady made me feel as if I were lying, repeating several times that "the order doesn't say that," despite my insistence. Eventually, the gentleman who took my order came over and confirmed to her that I was indeed correct. However, she continued arguing with him in front of me, making the entire situation even more uncomfortable.
To make matters worse, I later realized that additional items were still missing from my order, and I had to go through the same process again. The attitude and behavior I encountered today were extremely disappointing. I believe customer service should prioritize respect and resolution, not confrontation. At no point did anyone apologize for the mistake or the unpleasant treatment.

I hope Panera Bread addresses this situation appropriately and provides better training to ensure that no other customer has to experience what my family and I went through today.
